\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b arvensis}: Stems up to 80 cm, usually much branched. Leaves 1·5-5 × 0·6-1·5 cm; lobes oblong or linear. Peduncles not or scarcely clavate. Ligules 5-14 × 2·5-5 mm, rarely pink. Outer receptacular scales linear-subulate, the inner oblanceolate. Tubular florets c. 4 mm. 2n = 18.{\i  Cultivated ground and waste places. Throughout the range of the species.}
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b incrassata} (Loisel.) Nyman,{\i  Consp.} 361 (1879): Like subsp. ({\b a}) but leaves with wider, elliptical lobes; peduncles more or less clavate and somewhat arcuate; receptacle more elongate in fruit; receptacular scales somewhat wider, abruptly acuminate; ligules up to 11 × 4 mm; tubular florets 3-3·5 mm.{\i  Waste places. S. Europe}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b cyllenea} (Halácsy) R. Fernandes,{\i  Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc. }{\b 70}: 11 (1975) ({\i A. cyllenea }Halácsy): Stems up to 22 cm, intricately branched, sometimes slightly thickened upwards. Leaves up to 2 cm. Ligules up to 6 × 3 mm. Receptacular scales oblanceolate, more rigid than in subsp. ({\b a}). Tubular florets c. 2·5 mm.{\i  Cultivated ground and roadsides.} Greece.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b d}) Subsp. {\b sphacelata} (C. Presl) R. Fernandes, {\i Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  70}: 12 (1975) ({\i A. sphacelata} C. Presl): Biennial (or perhaps sometimes perennial). Stems up to 30 cm, from a woody stock, rigid, simple or more or less branched. Leaves not more than 2(-4·5) cm, pectinate-laciniate at base. Involucral bracts often with brown scarious margin and apex. Receptacle 2-5 × 2-3 mm, shortly conical; scales oblanceolate, abruptly acuminate, rigid. Ligules 3·5-6·5 × 2·25-3 mm. Tubular florets sometimes purple.{\i  Mountain pastures. • S. Italy, Sicilia}.
