\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 30. A. werneri} Stoj. & Acht.,{\i  Sborn. Balg. Akad. Nauk.}{\b  61}: 85 (1941). Greyish-green appressed-hairy. Stems up to 20 cm, many, branched below the middle. Leaves oblong, pinnatisect to pinnatifid or entire and spathulate; segments 2-3 on each side, linear-lanceolate to oblong, obtuse, callose-mucronulate. Peduncles clavate in fruit. Involucre obconical; outer bracts triangular-lanceolate, the inner oblong, with hyaline margin and apex. Ligules deflexed, up to 3 × 2 mm. Disc 4-8 mm in diameter; tubular florets swollen and spongy below the middle. Receptacle 3 × 2·2 mm, acutely conical; scales spathulate-lanceolate, about as long as or slightly longer than florets. Achenes 1·8-2 mm, turbinate-obconical, scarcely striate, with a short auricle. •{\i  N. Aegean region} ({\i Ayios Evstratios}); Gr.
